e company's essential human resources and contributed to its overall financial health? What were the minor problems that went unnoticed until they grew difficult to manage? Illes includes an appendix of the questions asked of workers and managers, suggesting guidelines to minimize the disasters of sizing down.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aDownsizing of organizationszUtahzOremvCase studies. 0aPlant shutdownszUtahzOremvCase studies. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aLabor History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172576040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501725760423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501725760/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles